19/08/2003
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Association of Camp Inmates in Republika Srpksa (RS) released a statement in favour of institutional efforts to maintain the integrity of the republic on Monday (18 August). 
The nationalist group said it would continue to support the efforts of RS President Dragan Cavic, aimed at defending and protecting entity institutions. 
At the same time, the group rejected calls from Sarajevo to remove the adjective "Serb" from the titles of institutions and administrative buildings in the republic. 
(SRNA, BBC - 18/08/03)
